Trojans are malicious programs that secretly enter your device, often disguised as harmless apps or files. Once inside, they can spy on your activities, steal data, or even control your device without you knowing. Sometimes, a device may already be infected before you notice, making it risky to trust any app or message. Protecting your device with antivirus tools and cautious behavior helps, but awareness about trojans is key. Keywords: “trojan malware,” “device infection,” “malware stealth,” “antivirus protection.”